<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="Aink150-kilavi">
        talaimakaṉ vāyiṉmaṟuttuḻi ivaṉ niṉmēl toṭarcciyiṟ kuṟaivilaṉ aruḷumuṭaiyaṉ; ātalāl, nī ivaṉōṭupulattal takātu eṉa neruṅki vāyilnērvikkuntōḻikku avaḷ colliyatu</p>    <p xml:lang="en">
          Spoken by her to the confidante who agrees to letting [him] enter, when [the heroine] denied entry [to] the hero, [the confidante] saying ‘He is one without fault in his relationship to you. He is also possessing of kindness/grace. Because of that, you [being] displeased with him is not appropriate.
  </p>
 </div>      
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink152">
<l>veḷḷāṅ kurukiṉ piḷḷai cetteṉak</l>
<l>kāṇiya ceṉṟa maṭanaṭai nārai</l>
<l>kaiyaṟu piraṟṟu kāṉalam pulampan</l>
<l>turaivaṉ varaiyu meṉpa</l>
<l>vaṟavaṉ pōlu maruḷumā ratuvē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>They say the man from the shore - the man from the ghat</l>
       <l> With the seashore-grove,</l>
       <l>The wader with an inexperienced gait having cried helplessly</l>
        <l>When [it] went to see, since the hatchling of the white wader died,</l>
       <l> Will marry [her].</l>
        <l>It is a rare thing how he graces [her] like a man of duty.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
